Barton County Health Department and Home Health Agency
Yesterday at 10:59 PM ·

September 11, 2020

The Barton County Health Department is announcing that one student at Lamar High School and two students at Lamar Middle School have tested positive for COVID-19. The high school student last attended class on September 9th and the middle school students last attended class on September 8th. All three students were asymptomatic while at school. The BCHD is working closely with the school district to identify all close contacts. Those who are identified as close contacts will be contacted by health department representatives and advised on how to proceed.

To protect the privacy of the individual and their family, we will not release individually identifiable details. The individuals are quarantined and being monitored closely by the Barton County Health Department.

Great news Tigers!

We are happy to announce that beginning Monday, September 14, 2020, ALL students will have the opportunity to eat breakfast and lunch for FREE through an extended waiver from the USDA!

This free meal service will be available to students in our buildings through December 31, 2020 or until Federal funds are exhausted. If you have paid ahead on lunches, your money will still be there when we go back to charging for meals. Also, please continue to submit Free & Reduced Family Meal applications so benefits are in place when the waiver ends.

We hope this service will help many students!

post_text:
TO: Special Education Parents/Guardians/Students,

The state department of special education has released new guidelines/forms that need to be completed if a school closure occurs. The case manager for your student’s services will be contacting you to discuss the best options and course of action necessary for your student to receive appropriate services during those times when we are unable to be in the building. Case managers will begin contacting parents the week of August 17th .

All students have the option of virtual or building instruction this year. The virtual program Launch will provide a grade level curriculum with some accommodations/modifications when necessary. The Special Education services will be addressed with Lamar school staff; essentially the IEP team. That team will come up with the plan necessary to address goals in a virtual environment. These are unprecedented times and we must continue to work as a team in order to best meet the needs of all our students.

post_text:
Transportation
While the Lamar R-I School District aims to provide transportation for all students, we encourage families to transport their children to and from school or carpool if possible for the 20/21 school year. This will place fewer students on routes and allow for better social distancing. Parents are expected to screen their child before sending them to school.

Buses will have a seating chart. Masks will be required on the bus for all students and staff. In addition, transportation staff will be sanitizing busses after each bus route.

Additional information will be available this week on how to sign students up for transportation.

Complete pages 1-5 of the physical form and leave the back page of the form blank for the healthcare provider to complete. You may go to the below link, scroll down and click on the "school physical form" to print.

Barton County Health Department and Home Health Agency
June 3 at 10:17 PM ·

A COUNTY-WIDE School Physical & *School Shot Clinic is scheduled for July 1, 2020 from 1:00 – 4:00 pm at the Lamar High School, 503 Maple Street in Lamar, MO. Both clinics are for student athletes from the Golden City, Lamar, & Liberal school districts. Signed consent forms are required for physicals & shots - both forms MUST be signed by a parent or guardian. Check your school’s Facebook page & website for more information.

*Students entering the 8th & 12th grades are required by the
State of Missouri to have the following shots:

• 8th Grade: 1 dose of Tdap (tetanus, diphtheria, acellular
pertussis) & 1 dose of meningococcal (MCV4)

o 11 year olds can get the Tdap & MCV4 shots now & will be up-to-
date upon entering the 8th Grade!

• 12th Grade: 1 dose of meningococcal (MCV4)

o 16 year olds can get the MCV4 shot now & will be up-to-date
upon entering the 12th Grade!

The HPV shot will also be offered to students 11 – 18 years of age It is recommended by the CDC but is NOT a requirement for school attendance in Missouri.

Kindergarten students attending summer school will be required to be up-to-date on their immunizations. Vaccination records must be on file by the first day of summer school or they will not be able to attend.

You may choose to take your child to his/her healthcare provider or the Barton County Health Department. The health department is asking for everyone to make an appointment prior. Their # is 417-682-3363.

Once your child receives the immunization, you may send the documentation to the school at 202 West 7th St, Lamar, MO attention Diana Ball or email it to dball@lamar.k12.mo.us.

Lamar Middle School is with Tamara Cole.
May 19 at 2:19 AM ·

It’s always great to share the success of our students. Every year each grade level chooses one girl and one boy to win the citizenship award. It is always a very difficult decision because we have so many kids deserving of this honor. It is a really big deal and quite an achievement. Since we couldn’t have our awards assemblies, we had yard signs made. Principal Ray and some teachers went around to deliver the signs and inform the students and families of their accomplishment.
The 6th grade winners were Calli and Henry.
The 7th grade winners were Kayelee and TJ.
The 8th grade winners were Madalyn and Alex. Congrats to these students and their families.

post_text:
Hello, LHS Seniors.
I know many of you have been anxiously waiting to find out if you received any local scholarships and/or awards. Well, the waiting is over. Please gather your family members around a big screen and click on the link below to view our scholarship slideshow:

https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vRLGn9kdoRgKik7yW5O1zcNhVcaQIFoAdNqlcQnsFtHxcDiz94jyI2xc44gspsOuiLegPfJ9M8Tw7Bm/pub?start=true&loop=false&delayms=5000

If you received a scholarship, you will be given a certificate, instructions, and contact information for the awarding scholarship committee, whenever you pick up your diploma in the front office on or after May 26th. You can then send a thank you card to the committee. We are truly blessed to live in such a generous community that is so willing to invest in your future.

Congratulations on all your hard work and accomplishments over the past four years. It's been very special to me to watch you grow and change and excel.

See you Sunday for the parade!
I'm excited for you!
Mrs. Hall

Lamar High School Students:

With the early school closure the Lamar yearbook staff decided to see if you can help them create some content for the 2019-20 LAMAR Tiger Yearbook.

Help them document what YOU and your FAMILY did during these trying times. Please send photos / selfies, or any writings, journals, etc. of your lives during this "Wellness Break". They will use these photos and writings to create some pages in the yearbook with 'real-life' documentation of what LHS students are doing during this uncertain time. Obviously, whatever you send in would become property of the yearbook staff and may or may not be used in the yearbook depending upon appropriateness, layout / space, etc.

If you would like to participate in this "hopefully" once in a lifetime activity, please send all photos and writings to Mrs. Willhite using her school gmail willhiteh@lamar.k12.mo.us. BE SURE to identify who's in the photo and what is going on.

Hey Tigers!

Just a reminder that our Grab & Go meal program is still available and free to all children 18 years old and younger. Our Grab & Go program continues to be allowable under the Missouri Stay at Home Order. Missourians are allowed to leave their home to access food and participate in drive-thru or pick-up meal options throughout the duration of the order.

Please remember to stay in your vehicle when picking up meals.

Grab & Go is available for pick up from 9:30 - 11:00 M-F at our West location with the exception of this Friday (4/10) and Monday (4/13). Meals will be handed out on Thursday, April 9th for all three days. Please remember to watch our Facebook page with additional announcements regarding the Grab & Go meal program. Stay well Tigers!

The Lamar R-1 School District is accepting sealed bids for the sale of two surplus pickup trucks and two timpani drums (pair). The two surplus trucks are: 1993 F-150 and a 1996 Chevy 1500 extended cab 4x4. Both trucks have a minimum bid of $500 and may be viewed by calling (417) 682-3384 to make an appointment between the hours of 8:15a.m. and 2:00p.m.

Bid specifications and instructions may be obtained by picking up a “Surplus Truck/Equipment” form from the Lamar Career and Technical Center, 501 Maple, Lamar, MO 64759. Sealed bids will be accepted until 9:00AM, March 17, 2020 at which time bids will be publicly opened. All bid envelopes shall be properly sealed and respective bids marked on the envelope and mailed or delivered to Lamar R-1 Superintendents Office, 202 W. 7th, Lamar, MO 64759. The Board reserves the right to accept or reject any or all bids.

High School: Today is "Celebrate YOU" Workshop Day.
22 different sessions were available throughout the day for students to learn about real-life skills from community members. Sessions included (but not limited to): Self-defense, Making Decisions, Financial Planning, Job/Interview/Application Skills, Automobile, Home & Pet Care, Yoga, Relationships, Art, Cooking, Parenting, Stress/Anxiety/Anger Management.
text:
High School: Today is "Celebrate YOU" Workshop Day.
22 different sessions were available throughout the day for students to learn about real-life skills from community members. Sessions included (but not limited to): Self-defense, Making Decisions, Financial Planning, Job/Interview/Application Skills, Automobile, Home & Pet Care, Yoga, Relationships, Art, Cooking, Parenting, Stress/Anxiety/Anger Management.

post_text:
High School: Rachel’s Challenge was held on Wednesday 2/19/20. Students from Golden City, Jasper, Sheldon, and Liberal joined our middle and high school students to hear the message of kindness and compassion. Students worked in small groups during the afternoon to come up with kindness projects to make our own do in our schools.

Hi-Step and Graphic Design partnered to design and sell "Be Kind" shirts. Anyone who wants to purchase their own shirt can contact LCTC @ 417-682-3384 or LHS for more information.

Congratulations to the Lamar High School Tiger Pride Band! They have been competing in San Antonio, TX this week. They received the Outstanding music, outstanding marching, outstanding general effect, and outstanding color Guard trophy. They also received 1st place in the parade review! A huge thank you to Mrs. Payne & Mr. Smith for their dedication to our students as well as thank you to parents, community supporters, chaperones, and finally, our students! Way to go Tigers!

Pictures from Lamar Tiger Pride Bands Facebook page.
